# Constitution

**Read before any work.** Specs implement features; ADRs are immutable unless human adds superseding ADR.

## ADR Index (docs/adr/)

| ADR | Rule |
|-----|------|
| 001 | Python + Tkinter only — no C++/Electron/Qt |
| 002 | Local-first `~/.personal_dev_tracker/` — no cloud in core |
| 003 | matplotlib lazy-loaded only |
| 004 | SQLite for fitness Phase 2+ only |
| 005 | 8 fixed category names — no renames without migration spec |
| 006 | Progression is DAG — validate cycles |
| 007 | **No code without approved spec** — spec is source of truth |
| 008 | Local multi-profile accounts (isolated data per profile) |
| 009 | Standalone EXE — user data in `~/.personal_dev_tracker/`, not beside EXE |

## If Code Conflicts With Spec or ADR

1. Stop implementing.
2. Update spec (revision history) or add ADR.
3. Get human approval.
4. Re-implement.

Never hotfix code that drifts from docs.

## Performance Budget

- Dashboard < 2s cold start
- matplotlib NOT at module import
- Minimal deps: stdlib + matplotlib only

## Human Writes Zero Application Code

Human approves PRD, ADRs, and specs. Agents implement, test, loop until AC pass.
